First Man: The Life of Neil A. Armstrong is the official biography of Neil Armstrong, the astronaut who became the first man to walk on the Moon on July 20, 1969. Written by James R. Hansen, it was published in 2005 by Simon & Schuster. The book describes Armstrong's involvement in the United States space program, culminating with the fateful Apollo 11 mission, while also detailing his personal life and upbringing.
The book has received a warm reception from several individuals associated with astronomy and the promotion of spaceflight. Examples include American media figure Walter Cronkite and English public intellectual Sir Patrick Moore.
